Sentencas: The synthesis via spray pyrolysis was investigated of lanthanum ferrite films doped with strontium and cobalt (LSCF) on silicon substrates for application as cathodes in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Low temperature synthesis by spray pyrolysis of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.2Fe0.8O3 thin films using ethanol and water as a solvent and their micro structural characterization

Sentencas: The following precursors were utilized: La(NO3)(3)center dot 6H(2)O, SrCl2 center dot 6H(2)O, CO (NO3)(2)center dot 6H(2)O, and Fe(NO3)(3)center dot 9H(2)O, with La:Sr:Co:Fe (9:1:2:8) stoichiometry.
Titulo: Low temperature synthesis by spray pyrolysis of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.2Fe0.8O3 thin films using ethanol and water as a solvent and their micro structural characterization

Sentencas: A solution of water and ethanol (1:3 proportion) was used.
Titulo: Low temperature synthesis by spray pyrolysis of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.2Fe0.8O3 thin films using ethanol and water as a solvent and their micro structural characterization

Sentencas: The relation among the morphology of the films, i) the temperature of the substrate and the distance of deposition was investigated.
Titulo: Low temperature synthesis by spray pyrolysis of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.2Fe0.8O3 thin films using ethanol and water as a solvent and their micro structural characterization

Sentencas: The results indicate that it is possible to obtain the LSCF film with a porous morphology at 200 degrees C and at a distance of deposition of 120 mm.
Titulo: Low temperature synthesis by spray pyrolysis of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.2Fe0.8O3 thin films using ethanol and water as a solvent and their micro structural characterization

Sentencas: This morphology is adequate for applications of LSCF as a cathode for use in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Low temperature synthesis by spray pyrolysis of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.2Fe0.8O3 thin films using ethanol and water as a solvent and their micro structural characterization
